{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> φρόνιμ-ος</b>, ον, <br /> also η, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.1070b\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]:— <b>in one's right mind, in one's senses,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 259 (_anapaest meter_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>showing presence of mind,</b> ἐν τοῖς δεινοῖς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.6.7; τὸ φ. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>presence of mind,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “HG” 2.3.56. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>sensible, prudent,</b> opposed to ἄφρων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Gorgias Rhetor et Sophista “fragment” 6; ψυχή 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 247a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἀνόητος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 2.14 (_comparative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν φρόνιμον ζητοῦντας.. ὥσπερ ἀποδεδρακότα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Bato Comicus 2.3; ὡς ἂν ὁ φ. ὁρίσειε 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1107a1, +others\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; φ. περί τινος <b>possessing sagacity</b> or <b>discernment</b> in a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.15, 21 (_comparative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; περί τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 490b (_comparative_), 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.161 (_comparative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἴς τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Alcaeus1.125a; ἐν τῷ σίτῳ φ. καὶ μέτριοι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.2.17. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> of thoughts, acts, and the like, φ. τι ἐργάσασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 42; φιλόπολις ἀρετή, φρόνιμος [prev. work] 547 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> of birds as giving omens, τοὺς ἄνωθεν φρονιμωτάτους οἰωνούς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1058 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.3.b</b></Level4> <b>sagacious,</b> of animals, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 263d, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 488b15, “PA” 648a8 (_comparative_), 687a8 (_superlative_), “GA” 753a11 (_comparative_), +others \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.4</b></Level3> τὸ φ. <b>practical wisdom, prudence,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 52.9 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 586d, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to τὸ ἄφρον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phdr.” 235e; ἰέναι ἐπὶ τὸ φρονιμώτερον 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 8.14: _plural_, ἄπορος ἐπὶ φρόνιμα\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] helpless in point of <b>wisdom,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 692 (Lyric poetry); τὰ -ώτερα ποιεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.211. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.5</b></Level3> <i>adverb</i> <b>-μως</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1364, “Av.” 1333 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 192e, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἀλόγως, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 3.9; φ. ἔχειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.3.57; διακεῖσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.114 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> φρονιμώτερον, διακεῖσθαι τῶν ἄλλων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.10 \">Refs</a>]; <b>-ωτέρως</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. author] 13.15 \">Refs</a>]: <i>superlative</i> -ώτατα, λέγειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Apologia Socratis” 20. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5430","accentedUnicode":"φρονίμως","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5429","matchingForm":"φρόνιμος","stepTransliteration":"fronimos","gloss":"thoughtful","_zh_tw_Gloss":"聰明, 有見識","_es_Gloss":"prudente","_zh_Gloss":"聪明, 有见识"}],"shortDef":"shrewdly, wisely","mediumDef":"shrewdly, wisely <br /><b>considerately, providently, wisely</b> <ref='Luk.16.8'>Lk. 16:8</ref>*","stepGloss":"shrewdly","stepTransliteration":"fronimōs","count":1,"_es_Definition":"adv. sabiamente, sagazmente","_zh_tw_Definition":"精明地, 聰明地 (路 16:8)","_zh_Definition":"精明地, 聪明地 (路 16:8)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"khôn ngoan; sáng suốt.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"聰明","_es_Gloss":"astutamente","_zh_Gloss":"聪明"}]}